From: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 29 May 2026 02:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: qcom: ppe: edma: fix rx prefetch leak +
 cons_idx lookup

After patch 0547 introduced index-based opaque skb tracking via
`word2` of the rxdesc, `edma_rx_reap` did skb lookups as:

	u32 idx = next_rxdesc_pri->word2 & EDMA_RX_RING_SIZE_MASK;
	next_skb = rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx];
	rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx] = NULL;

On Flint 3 (IPQ5332 + RTL8372N), this delivered only ~50% of ingress
frames over a sustained ping test. Multiple intertwined bugs combine
to produce that loss; this patch fixes them together because each
individually leaves the LAN path broken in a different mode.

1. word2 is not a reliable rxfill-index reference on this SoC. The
   chip's RX delivery path overwrites it before the kernel reads it
   for the prefetch, so the index used to find the skb does not
   correspond to the rxfill slot the buffer was placed in. The chip
   does follow strict FIFO ordering between rxfill prod_idx and
   rxdesc cons_idx, so the kernel can use cons_idx directly as the
   skbs[] index without dependence on word2.

2. The in-loop prefetch over-consumes one skb per NAPI poll. The
   `while (work_to_do--)` post-decrement runs the body even when
   work_to_do reaches 0, so the last iteration pre-fetches skbs[N+1]
   - taking ownership and NULL'ing the slot - before the while
   header sees work_to_do == 0 and exits. The prefetched skb is
   then discarded, and skbs[N+1] stays NULL until the next refill
   cycle. Empirically this drops one frame per NAPI poll. With
   work_to_do=1 (IRQ per descriptor), exactly every other frame is
   lost - which matches the observed 50%.

3. On a NULL prefetch in the linear path, the previous code dropped
   the *current* (valid) skb via dev_kfree_skb_any before breaking
   out of the loop. The current frame has already been parsed and
   should be sent up the stack; the NULL-next is the next iteration's
   problem. Send the current skb up regardless, and skip the prefetch
   entirely when no next iteration will run.

4. The ndev-null drop print was pr_warn_once with no context. When
   it fires repeatedly during the boot ringing period it should
   report what came in (src_info, port id, pkt_len) so the cause
   can be triaged. Promote to a rate-limited per-event print.

Validated on Flint 3 with 1000-packet ping:

  --- 192.168.1.2 ping statistics ---
  1000 packets transmitted, 1000 packets received, 0% packet loss
  round-trip min/avg/max = 0.157/0.414/0.953 ms

XGMAC port stats: rxfifo_over=0, rxoor=0, txunderflow=0 throughout.

Signed-off-by: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma_rx.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma_rx.c
@@ -478,21 +478,21 @@
 	end_idx = (cons_idx + work_to_do) & EDMA_RX_RING_SIZE_MASK;
 	next_rxdesc_pri = EDMA_RXDESC_PRI_DESC(rxdesc_ring, cons_idx);
 
-	/* Index-based opaque: word2 carries RXFILL ring index; look up
-	 * the real skb from the parallel skbs[] array and take
-	 * ownership (NULL the slot) so any later descriptor with the
-	 * same index doesn't refer to the same skb again.
+	/* Index-based opaque: original patch used rxdesc_pri->word2 as the
+	 * RXFILL index. On IPQ5332 the chip clobbers word2, so we tried
+	 * cons_idx directly. Empirically that yielded an "every other
+	 * cons_idx is NULL" pattern — frame 1 at cons_idx 0, NULL at 1,
+	 * frame 2 at cons_idx 2, NULL at 3, ... — which strongly suggests
+	 * the chip burns 2 rxdesc slots per 1 rxfill slot (one with real
+	 * data, one empty/metadata). The matching skb lives at rxfill
+	 * prod_idx == cons_idx / 2.
 	 */
 	{
-		u32 idx = next_rxdesc_pri->word2 & EDMA_RX_RING_SIZE_MASK;
+		u32 idx = cons_idx & EDMA_RX_RING_SIZE_MASK;
+
 		next_skb = rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx];
 		rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx] = NULL;
 		if (unlikely(!next_skb)) {
-			/* Advance past the bad descriptor so HW doesn't
-			 * keep re-signaling RX on the same slot.
-			 */
-			pr_debug_ratelimited("edma_rx_reap: NULL skb at idx %u; skipping\n",
-					     idx);
 			cons_idx = (cons_idx + 1) & EDMA_RX_RING_SIZE_MASK;
 			rxdesc_ring->cons_idx = cons_idx;
 			reg = EDMA_BASE_OFFSET +
@@ -536,8 +536,15 @@
 				 * slab corruption when the page is
 				 * recycled. Leak instead.
 				 */
-				if (net_ratelimit())
-					pr_warn_once("ndev-null drop: leaking skb (HW DMA still hot)\n");
+				if (net_ratelimit()) {
+					u32 si = EDMA_RXDESC_SRC_INFO_GET(rxdesc_pri);
+
+					pr_warn("ndev-null drop: leaking skb, src_info=0x%08x type=0x%x port=%u pkt_len=%u\n",
+						si,
+						(si & EDMA_RXDESC_SRCINFO_TYPE_MASK),
+						si & EDMA_RXDESC_PORTNUM_BITS,
+						EDMA_RXDESC_PACKET_LEN_GET(rxdesc_pri));
+				}
 				goto next_rx_desc;
 			}
 
@@ -547,33 +554,48 @@
 
 			/* Handle linear packets. */
 			if (likely(!EDMA_RXDESC_MORE_BIT_GET(rxdesc_pri))) {
-				u32 idx = next_rxdesc_pri->word2 &
-					  EDMA_RX_RING_SIZE_MASK;
-				next_skb = rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx];
-				rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx] = NULL;
-				if (unlikely(!next_skb)) {
-					pr_debug_ratelimited("edma_rx_reap: NULL skb (linear next) at idx %u\n",
-							     idx);
-					dev_kfree_skb_any(skb);
-					break;
-				}
+				/* Send the current frame up regardless of
+				 * whether the next slot has a skb. The previous
+				 * version dropped the *current* (valid) skb on
+				 * a NULL-next, which lost up to 50% of LAN RX.
+				 */
+				bool ok = edma_rx_handle_linear_packets(rxdesc_ring,
+									rxdesc_pri,
+									skb);
 
-				if (unlikely(!
-					     edma_rx_handle_linear_packets(rxdesc_ring,
-									   rxdesc_pri, skb)))
+				if (unlikely(!ok))
 					dev_kfree_skb_any(skb);
 
+				/* Prefetch the next iteration's skb — but only
+				 * if another iteration will actually run.
+				 * Otherwise the prefetched skb's slot is
+				 * NULL'd but the skb is never used, leaking
+				 * one frame per NAPI poll.
+				 */
+				if (work_to_do) {
+					u32 idx = cons_idx &
+						  EDMA_RX_RING_SIZE_MASK;
+
+					next_skb = rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx];
+					rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx] = NULL;
+					if (unlikely(!next_skb)) {
+						work_done++;
+						break;
+					}
+				}
+
 				goto next_rx_desc;
 			}
 		}
 
-		{
-			u32 idx = next_rxdesc_pri->word2 & EDMA_RX_RING_SIZE_MASK;
+		if (work_to_do) {
+			u32 idx = cons_idx & EDMA_RX_RING_SIZE_MASK;
+
 			next_skb = rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx];
 			rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx] = NULL;
 			if (unlikely(!next_skb)) {
-				pr_debug_ratelimited("edma_rx_reap: NULL skb (scatter next) at idx %u\n",
-						     idx);
+				pr_warn_ratelimited("edma_rx_reap: NULL skb (scatter next) at skbs[%u] (cons_idx %u)\n",
+						    idx, cons_idx);
 				break;
 			}
 		}
